  "response": "The chemical formula for elemental zinc is simply \"Zn.\" This is determined based on the fact that zinc is a chemical element, and elements are represented by their chemical symbols. The chemical symbol \"Zn\" is derived from the Latin word \"zincum.\" Since zinc is a pure substance consisting of only one type of atom, it doesn't combine with any other elements to form compounds in its natural state, so no additional numbers or elements are needed to represent it in its uncombined form.",
